         <abstract>
            <p>This paper demonstrates that different state space specifications in a Markov chain framework can provide straightforward but powerful tools in forecasting accounts receivable and analyzing payment behavior. These characteristics are demonstrated using a sample of retail revolving credit accounts for a large New York department store over the period October 1979 to May 1981.</p>
         </abstract>
